title: cheese whiz
directions: Melt cheese and milk.
Add mustard and vinegar.
Put in container and refrigerate.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all together with hands and shape into a ring. Put strawberry jam or green pepper jam in center and serve with crackers of your choice.

title: crock-pot mushroom barley soup
directions: Microwave meat first, or else put in crock-pot and cook until half done.
Add barley and mushrooms, fill pot to within 1 inch of top with stock or water.
Cook 3 to 4 hours until barley is done. Season to taste.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on cake while hot.
Brown under broiler until coconut is brown.

title: short'nin bread
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add butter.
Place on floured board; pat to thickness of 1/2-inch.
Cut into shapes desired.
Bake in a moderate oven (325° to 350°) for 25 minutes.

title: neiman marcus cookies
directions: Cream the butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix together with the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Add chocolate chips, Hershey Bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place two inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. makes 55-60 cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add 3 tablespoons jello powder and red food coloring.
Let cool.
Place washed strawberries in baked pie shell.
Cover with above mixture. Chill; serve with Cool Whip.

title: pork chops
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Put pork chops in and shake until flour covers chops.
Put Crisco in frying pan.
One at a time, put chops in pan.
Cook on medium heat until done.

title: very berry surprise
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple (save juice).
Mix Jell-O with package directions (hot water only).
Add juice from berries and pineapple.
Let jell.
Add pineapple and blueberries to Jell-O. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Top chilled Jell-O mixture and chill.

title: corn bread mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in shortening. Store in an airtight container.
Take the amount that you think you need and add egg and water.
Bake until golden brown.

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: *Add more bread crumbs to taste.

title: watergate salad(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Mix all the ingredients in order listed. Cool before serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Heat liquid to boil.
Dissolve Jello and let cool slightly. By spoonful, add ice cream until all is in and melted.
Chill for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes and fold in fruit.
Mix well.
Chill till set.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine the sugar with flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like crumbs. Stir in molasses and egg.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls - no bigger- and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately because cookies firm quickly as they cool.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies. These are good and easy to make.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put oleo, cocoa and buttermilk in saucepan.
Heat over low heat, do not boil; remove and stir in sugar, pecans and vanilla. Beat, then spread while cake is still hot and serve.
Wonderful!

title: sausage rings
directions: Mix Bisquick and water well.
Roll the dough mixture thin. Spread the sausage in a thin layer over the dough.
Roll from each end toward the middle for 2 rolls.
Cut down the middle and wrap in Handi-Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight for easier slicing or freeze for several weeks.
Slice 1/2 inch rings.
Bake in 400° oven until slightly brown, around 20 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Bring shortening, water, margarine and cocoa to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk (sour cream can be substituted), eggs, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 12 x 17-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: triple chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large pan, cook pudding with milk as directed on package.
Blend dry cake mix thoroughly into hot pudding; beat one or two minutes.
(You don't add eggs or other ingredients listed on cake mix.)
Pour into greased, floured pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate bits. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: jumbo pasta shells
directions: Save 1 cup Mozzarella cheese for topping.

title: angel food delight
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler; add beaten egg yolk and cool.
Add beaten egg whites, sugar and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put broken pieces of cake in bottom of pan.
Pour cool mixture over the pieces of cake.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cook eggs; remove shells and cut each in half lengthwise. Remove yolks.
Mix yolks with rest of ingredients.
Fill each half white of egg with mixture.

title: microwave garlicy potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to coat potatoes.
Cover tightly with microwave plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 10 minutes in a 600 to 700 watt oven or 15 minutes in a 400 to 500 watt oven, shaking dish to redistribute potatoes.
Potatoes are done when the tip of a small knife easily pierces the potato in the center.
Serves 4 as a side dish.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour with the sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in a saucepan.
Warm over low heat to 115° to 120°.
(Margarine does not have to be melted.)
Remove from heat and gradually add flour mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Add 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in additional flour to form soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn over and grease top.
Let rise 15 minutes. Turn out on a floured board.
Divide dough in half and shape into rolls.
Cover and let rest in a warm place for 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown and not runny.

title: danish sesame bran bread
directions: Combine boiling water and cornmeal.
Combine 1 1/2 cups unbleached flour, 1 cup whole wheat flour, cereal, sesame seed, salt and yeast; blend well.
Heat milk, oil, molasses and honey until very warm.
Add warm liquid, cornmeal mixture and yogurt to flour mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in rest of whole wheat flour until stiff dough forms.
Knead in 1 to 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour about 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dorothy's candy
directions: Melt chocolate very slowly in double boiler; add rest of ingredients.
Spread on wax paper; chill.
Break into pieces.

title: ham and white bean soup
directions: Dice and saute celery, onion, carrots, zucchini, and ham in dutch oven with
olive oil and seasoning.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, spinach, 1 can beans (smashed), and 2 cups water. Heat to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add the rest of beans and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: frosted coffee bars
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven. Frost with powdered sugar frosting, flavored with coffee.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: Trim fat; slice meat into thin strips.
Combine salad oil, sugar, cornstarch and pepper sauce and add meat strips.
Cut vegetables up.

title: crunchy broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar to make dressing.
Set aside.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Combine shrimp, carrots, onions and peppers; set aside.
Mix well soup, vinegar, salad oil, sugar and mustard.
Pour over shrimp and vegetables.
Mix lightly.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, add cucumber slices.
(You can also add orange or apple slices, dew melon cubes, etc.).
Serves 6.

title: potatoes and tomatoes with fresh coconut
directions: Peel potatoes, then dice into 3/4-inch pieces and put into bowl of cold water.
Heat oil in heavy 3-quart pot over medium-high flame.
When hot, add finely chopped garlic.
Stir about 5 seconds before adding red pepper and cumin seed.
Stir for another 3 seconds.
Garlic should brown lightly, red pepper should darken and cumin seed should sizzle.
Lower heat to medium.
Add grated coconut and stir for 10 to 15 seconds.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; sift baking powder and flour together and add to butter mixture, alternating with egg yolks. Add lemon extract, fruits and nuts; add stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: frozen cheese salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir eggs into pumpkin.
Blend salt, sugar and spices.
Stir into pumpkin.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer chicken.
Melt margarine and add flour until smooth, add sour cream until it just bubbles.
Add soup, chilies and onion salt.
Blend well, pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and bake until melted.
Serve over rice.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix sour cream and soda in separate bowl and let stand until foamy.
Add sour cream mixture to egg and sugar mixture and mix well.
Pour into four greased and floured loaf pans (or 10 mini loaf pans 2/3 of the way full).
Bake 50 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Drain.
Stir in water, catsup and mustard; season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Top with cheese; cover. Let stand until cheese melts.
Makes 4.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook, peel and slice fresh beets in a bowl and set aside.

Mix sugar and cornstarch until blended before adding the vinegar. Stir all ingredients together and cook at hard boiling point for 1 to 2 minutes or until clear and slightly thickened. Add butter and pour this sauce over the beets.
Serve warm.
May be reheated, but do not boil.
If there is extra sauce, it may be used later if stored in refrigerator.
A small family would not use 3 cups of beets at one meal.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Soak
beans
in
broth.
Cook down with garlic that has been minced.
Add
onions,
celery
and carrots, all chopped. Add eggplant, peeled and chopped, and olive oil.
Season with herbs. Cook on very low burner until done.

title: favorite pumpkin pie
directions: Mix squash, nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
(May need to cover edges of pie with foil to prevent overbrowning.)

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: bulls eye breakfast
directions: Cut hole in bread with biscuit cutter.
Spray cooking spray in frying pan.
Place bread with hole in pan; cook on medium heat. Break egg into bowl, then pour into hole in bread.
Cook until almost set; turn.
Put circle cut from bread into pan while egg finishes cooking.
Remove from pan and serve hot.
Makes 1 serving.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Prepare chicken by removing bones and steaming good size pieces (good idea to buy breasts and thighs).
Dip in tempura batter and fry in hot deep oil.
Slice each piece in 1/2-inch to 1-inch slices.
Arrange on a bed of shredded lettuce.
Cover with sauce.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Blend sour cream and dry mustard; set aside.
Slice cucumber and place in shallow dish.
Pour sour cream mix over all.
Chill. Serve cold.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook all except vinegar and salt.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours.
Add vinegar and salt when beans are tender (last).

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package and drain. Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: city chicken
directions: You will also need sticks.

title: trifle pudding
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 340° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put in bottom of container and layer shredded lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Place cheese on top. Serve with nacho chips.

title: spam and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain and set aside.
Cut Spam into small cubes.
Set aside.
In a pot big enough for all ingredients, melt margarine.
Add Spam and cook it for a few minutes.
Add macaroni and all-purpose seasoning and pepper. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: fried squid(calamari fritti)
directions: Cut
squid
into
rings or 3-inch pieces.
If tentacles are large,
cut
in half.
Toss the squid in flour mixed with salt and
pepper;
coat
as
you
are
frying, to avoid flour getting soggy.
In a skillet, heat enough oil to measure about 1
to
inches
deep.
When
the oil is hot, add squid. Lower
heat just
a
little
and
continue to fry squid until nicely
golden. Drain on paper towels.
The squid should cook in
to 3 minutes. Place fried squid on platter and garnish with lemon wedges. Makes 2 servings.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: In a large saucepan, mix together the corn syrup and sugar and heat slowly until it boils, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until it melts.
Then stir in Rice Krispies. Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, melt chips and spread on top.

title: hawaiian teriyaki steak
directions: Mix together soy sauce, sugar, ginger and garlic powder.
Add meat strips and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Cook on barbecue grill on bamboo sticks after draining.

title: cheese and chile dip
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a bowl and beat at medium speed with mixer until smooth.
If you use a food processor, use the knife blade.
Drain the can of chiles.
Gently stir in the last three ingredients.
Chill well.
If you wish, garnish with chile strip.
Set out at room temperature before serving, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rock candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is dissolved.
Cook over high heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from heat and add desired flavoring or cinnamon oil.
Add food coloring if desired.
Pour into cookie sheet; allow to cool completely.
Crack candy and roll into powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a glass pie plate.
Needs no crust.
Bake at 325° until browns on top.

title: creamy sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until fork easily pierces potatoes.
Cool slightly. Remove skins. Place cooked and peeled potatoes into a large mixing bowl.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth. There should be 3 1/2 cups of mashed sweet potatoes. Stir in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in spices, salt and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: bread pudding with lemon sauce
directions: Butter square Corning baking dish. Put bread in dish.
Mix scalding milk, butter, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg, stir over bread.
Set baking dish in some water in Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in dishpan in order given.
Drop by large tablespoon or ice cream scoop and flatten.
Place 6 to a cookie sheet.
Recipe does not call for flour.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 77 large cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
In another bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Gradually add dry mixture to liquids and mix well.
If you wish, stir in 1/2 cup nuts and/or raisins.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for about 1 hour or until it springs back when lightly touched and sides of the loaf have pulled away from the pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Stir well.
Pour half (about 2 1/2 cups) in a greased pan.
Let jell, about 30 minutes.
Spread sour cream on top.
Add the other half of strawberry mixture.
Let jell.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Add egg yolk and yeast mixture.
Divide into 2 parts and roll out on cookie sheet.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Top with other crust.
Bake at 350°.

title: super simple supper soup
directions: Bring all ingredients, except macaroni, to a boil.
Add macaroni and simmer until tender.
Serves lots.

title: lemon pudding
directions: In saucepan, blend sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks or beaten egg.
Return to hot mixture; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; blend in butter, vanilla, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Pour into sherbet dishes; chill.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pot roast (beef or pork)
directions: I add 2 red peppers or 1 fresh jalapeno.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
You may add a little more milk if needed.
Drop by teaspoon into hot, boiling grease.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: frosty cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and pineapple.
Mix powdered sugar and sour cream together.
Stir into fruit.
Pour into shallow dish and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer and let sit a few minutes before serving.

title: heavenly lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine like pie crust, add nuts and press into bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes; cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar; fold in 1 c. Cool Whip then spread over crust.
Mix the pudding mix using only 3 c. milk, and beat until stiff; spread over the cream cheese mixture.
Top with the remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Chill well before serving.

title: sweet-sour carrots(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Peel carrots and cut into strips.
Cook until just tender; drain.
Add butter, sugar, vinegar and mint or dill.
Cook until transparent.
Serve hot or as a cold relish.

title: texas beef stew(serves 6)
directions: Cut steak in crosswise strips 1-inch wide.
Mix water and vinegar with ketchup and other seasonings; pour over meat.
Let stand several hours, turning meat occasionally.
Lift meat from liquid, saving vinegar mixture.
Place meat in pan, top with sliced onions and add 1/2 of the vinegar mixture.
Cover, simmer gently over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, adding vinegar mixture as required to keep liquid about 1/2-inch deep in pan.
Remove meat and onions to hot platter; strain liquid, then boil hard 3 to 4 minutes, pour over meat and serve while hot.

title: poteau french dressing
directions: This should be made just before serving.
Rub the bottom of a small bowl with onion or garlic.
Put in 1/2 teaspoon of salt, a dash of Tabasco sauce and a tablespoon of cold water (to dissolve salt).
Stir until salt is completely dissolved.
Now gradually add, stirring constantly, 6 tablespoons of oil and 1 teaspoon of vinegar or lemon juice.
Beat quickly until well mixed.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix butter, flour and chopped pecans.
Press in a casserole dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Add pie filling.
Eat!

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift flour; add baking soda and salt. Sift again. Combine with brown sugar. Add melted shortening to beaten eggs and combine with dry ingredients. Add nuts and dates. Pour into greased 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in bars while hot. Sprinkle or roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: 1. Have all ingredients measured and ready.
Line a baking sheet with waxed paper or foil; set aside.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water, set aside.
Add pineapple and sugar together in pot on stove.
Bring to a boil.
Add the gelatine mixture to the pineapple mixture.
Stir until gelatine is dissolved.
Add lemon and cherry juice, let cool.
Mash cream cheese and chopped cherries.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Chill to slightly thickened.
Add Cool Whip.
Top with chopped walnuts and cherries, if desired.
Mix with mixer in large bowl.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and banana.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Cool well and store overnight before cutting. Makes 1 loaf.

title: hopel-popel
directions: Place potatoes	in
a
medium bowl.
Cover with boiling water. Let
stand
for
8 minutes or until water is absorbed. Heat skillet
and add bacon.
Cook and stir until bacon begins to crisp.
Add
the
onion
and
mushrooms.
Stir until barely tender.
Add
parsley,
sprinkling	it
evenly
over the bacon mixture and
potatoes.
Toss together lightly.
Adjust heat to low.
In a small mixing bowl, beat eggs with 1/4 cup of water. Add the
salt
and
pepper.
Pour
over vegetables in skillet. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook
over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until eggs are set.
Cover skillet for part of cooking time to help eggs
set on top.
If desired, brown under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Put water and bouillon cubes in pot; boil until cubes are melted.
Add chopped broccoli, onion and celery (celery is a must).
Let boil until soft.
Melt butter and add flour.
Heat half and half in microwave, then add it to broccoli mixture.
Add butter and flour mixture.
Let simmer until it thickens.
Add parsley and dash of black pepper.
No salt is needed.

title: huckleberry muffins
directions: Combine oats and sour milk. Let stand.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add egg and melted butter to oat mixture and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Fold in huckleberries.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins. Peel and slice thin. Cook bacon until crisp, then cook onion in bacon fat. Mix in flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir water in gradually. Add vinegar gradually. Cook and stir until it boils for 1 minute. Pour over potatoes. Add the bacon. Cover and let stand until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Then add water.
Place in greased and floured pan. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Mix 3 beaten eggs. Mix pineapple and 1 tsp. vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie shells. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour long cake pan.
Sprinkle on bottom the pecans and coconut.
Mix cake mix and pour in pan.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar and spoon on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Prepare sweet dough. Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Roll dough into 12 x 9-inch rectangle. Sprinkle raisins on dough. From short end, roll dough jelly roll fashion.
Pinch seam to seal.
Press ends to seal and tuck under.
Place, seam side down, in pan. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped. Let cool on rack.

title: oats 'n pumpkin pinwheels
directions: Beat 1 cup sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Mix in egg whites.
Stir in combined flour, oats and baking soda.
On wax paper, press into 16 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread combined pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar and spice over dough to 1/2 inch from edge. From narrow end, roll up dough.
Sprinkle sesame seed around roll, pressing gently.
Wrap in wax paper; freeze overnight or until firm.

title: zero salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar with tightly fitted top. Shake well and refrigerate. Shake well before use.

title: mexican green peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seed.
Cook peppers 5 minutes in boiling water to cover (salt added).
Drain and set aside.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill peppers with meat mixture.
Place in a 2-quart shallow casserole.
Pour tomato sauce over and around the peppers.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole.
Layer sliced zucchini, sliced tomatoes, mushrooms and cheese.
Repeat to fill dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water in large container.
Add cold water and stir.
Add sugar and stir.
Add lemonade and stir.
Add pineapple juice and stir thoroughly.
Freeze in appropriate containers (large mouth plastic gallon jugs are good).
Let thaw until slushy before serving and add ginger ale.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and nuts; set aside.
Drain juice from cherries and pineapple; bring juice to a boil.
Pour over jello to dissolve.
Let cool; add Coke.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, butter, buttermilk, flour and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake until golden brown (approximately 50 minutes).
Let cool before slicing.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Cut rolls in half.
Spread sauce over bottom half of roll.
Sprinkle with ham and cheese.
Cover with top half of roll.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: b l t salad toss
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, salad dressing, green pepper and onion; toss lightly.
Chill.
Add bacon; toss lightly.
Spoon vegetable mixture over shredded lettuce.
Garnish with additional cherry tomato halves and bacon curls.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken until tender; allow to cool and cut into bite size pieces. Saute onion and green chilies in butter. Mix soup, milk and Velveeta cheese in large pan; heat until cheese melts. Add onions and green peppers. Stir until well combined. Add chicken and mix well. In a large baking dish, place a layer of tortillas, a layer of chicken mixture and a layer of grated cheese. Repeat layers until dish is filled. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: greek pizza
directions: Fry chopped meat and drain. Add tomatoes. Saute eggplant in olive oil, then add to meat mixture. Grate cheese. Set aside. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crescent rolls. Spread meat mixture on dough. Top with cheese and season to taste.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: fresh pickle slices
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients and then pour over cucumbers and onions.
Stir gently to mix. Refrigerate overnight.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add melted butter and milk. Blend together.
Batter should be moist and stiff.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling liquid.
Cover and cook 18 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen dumplings.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate (10 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat remaining ingredients after you sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.

title: chicken rice dish
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Remove chicken from bone and cut in chunks.
Saute chicken and mushrooms in butter or oleo. Add the chicken broth
and	green
beans
and
bring this to a boil.
Stir in Minute
rice, then remove from heat.
Cover for a few minutes before serving.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar; put dry cake mix on top.
Put pats of margarine on top.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 minutes or until top is brown and bubbly.
(Any flavor pie filling may be used.)

title: hungarian poppy seed nut slices
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes; add nuts and poppy seed.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in flour and salt. Refrigerate until dough is easily shaped into rolls.
Make 2 rolls.
Roll in sugar; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased pan at 325° for 20 minutes or until slightly brown.
Store in closed tin.

title: sesame stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Stir-fry garlic and onion 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, zucchini and mushrooms.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add water chestnuts and tomatoes; heat through.
Add Molly McButter; stir until melted in.
Sprinkle with sesame seed, basil and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 (2 cup) servings.

title: grilled salmon fillets(easy; see marinade variations)
directions: Make a marinade by mixing 2 tablespoons oil, ginger, cumin, coriander, salt and cayenne together in large shallow bowl. Add fish and marinate in the refrigerator for no more than 30 minutes. Meanwhile, build a single-level fire. Set grill rack in place. Cover grill with lid and
let rack heat up, about 5 minutes. Rub cooking grate with oil-dipped wad of paper towels.

title: irish whiskey cake
directions: Make yellow cake according to directions, except substitute double strength coffee for water called for.
Bake in two round layers.
When layers are cool, split them in half.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon whiskey on each cut, except for rounded top.
Spread Cool Whip on each cut surface and top.
Stack layers.
Refrigerate 8 hours (24 is better).

title: salsa fresca
directions: Gently stir together all ingredients in a small bowl until blended.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Put beef, soups, onion, salt and pepper into a large pot. Simmer slowly for several hours.
When the meat is tender, add sour cream and mushroom pieces.
Bring to a boil and immediately serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: nantucket cranberry pie
directions: Sprinkle 2 cups cranberries into buttered 10-inch pie plate. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and walnuts.
Sprinkle over berries.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust.

title: tapioca jello salad
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together until thick; let cool. Mix Dream Whip; add to cooled jello-pudding mixture, along with drained pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: cheeseburger logs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tomatoes and bread crumbs in a large bowl; let stand until liquid is absorbed.
Lightly mix in ground beef, egg, mustard, salt and pepper.
Divide mixture into quarters, then shape into a 5-inch loaf; make a ridge down middle of each with your finger.
Place loaves on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Spoon cheese into hollows.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts and loaves are crusty brown. Yields 4 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Brown on both sides.
Mix soup mix in 1 cup water.
Pour over steak and simmer on top of stove for 1 1/2 hours or until tender on low to medium heat. Soup mix will thicken into gravy.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes. (Dough does better if chilled.)

title: easy chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Break block of noodles; reserve seasoning packet.
Stir noodles, chicken, bok choy and carrot into water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in seasoning packet.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine with cocoa in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir into eggs, sugar, flour, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes. As soon as it is taken out of the oven, sprinkle miniature marshmallows or marshmallow cream on top.

title: mixed nut crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In large roasting pan, spread the popped corn and the dry roasted nuts.
In heavy saucepan, combine the sugar, butter and dark corn syrup.
Cook until mixture boils. Boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over corn and nuts; stir to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Cool; break apart.
Store in covered container.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Mix salt, pepper, paprika and flour in a plastic bag; add chicken, one piece at a time, and shake to coat.
Place butter and oil in a saute pan or large skillet; heat over medium heat until bubbly.
Add garlic and chicken; saute, turning, about 6 minutes or until chicken is brown and fork can be easily inserted.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of cooking fat from pan; add wine and deglaze pan, scraping up brown bits.
Add lemon juice and heat 1 minute; return chicken to pan; add lemon slices and heat 2 minutes.
Add capers and pimento.
Sprinkle chives over all.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook chicken and broccoli.
Layer in baking dish. Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and small pats of butter.
Bake at 400° until top is brown and bubbly.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Cream the butter; add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add flour and milk.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: roasted red peppers
directions: Place the peppers on a roasting tray and put in a 350° oven. Turn the peppers until cooked on all sides (about 1 hour).
When done, place the peppers in a paper bag.
Wait a few minutes and then peel and slice the peppers into strips.
Place in a bowl with fresh garlic and olive oil and let marinate.

title: salmon loaf # 1
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is crispy.
(Mixture will look sloppy.)
Good cold, too.

title: korean salad
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
In large salad bowl, mix spinach, sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and bacon.
In a jar, combine oil, sugar, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and onion; shake well.
Sprinkle dressing on salad and toss.
Serve. Dressing refrigerates well and is good on any salad.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook chicken (cut into pieces) in water with 1 teaspoon salt. Strain and debone.
Use 2 cups broth to cook rice.
Saute onion and broccoli in oleo.
Mix all together and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: okra casserole
directions: Cook and crumble meat.
Arrange in layers in casserole dish. Bake at 350° until vegetables are tender.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Combine oat bran, brown sugar, walnuts and baking powder in bowl; mix well.
Combine milk, bananas, egg whites and oil in small bowl; mix well.
Stir into oat bran mixture just until moistened.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 17 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces; set aside.
Sprinkle washed rice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour 2 cups water over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Place parsnips, cut in chunks, around chicken.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken. It will look very soupy.
Bake, covered, with foil at 325° for 60 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: potatoes and sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel the potatoes (enough to fill a 13 x 9-inch casserole bowl) and slice as thin as possible.
Grate the cheese.
Brown the sausage.
Alternate the layers of each, beginning with a layer of potato slices, then sausage and then cheese.
Add the milk, salt and pepper.
Bake in preheated 350° oven.
You may have to cover with foil.
For softer potatoes you may want to boil them for a few minutes before putting them in the casserole bowl.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Pick through crabmeat to remove cartilage.
Mix together all ingredients, except crabmeat, in medium bowl.
Gently fold in crab.
Shape into 8 crab cakes and place on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with paprika; place under preheated broiler until golden brown, about 7 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of the French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Place chicken, sliced onion, 2 teaspoons salt and celery in a pot.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Bone and cut chicken into pieces.
Reserve broth.
Combine soup, broth, tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon salt in pan and heat.
Layer chicken, tortillas, cheese, chopped onion and heated sauce in a casserole dish. Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Lower to 200° and bake for 40 more minutes.
May be frozen.

title: ron's biscuits
directions: Dump all in big bowl and mix really good.
Sprinkle pastry cloth well with flour and roll dough out like a cross.
Take left side; fold to center.
Take right side; fold to center.
Take bottom; fold up.
Take top and fold down.
Roll over slightly with rolling pin, then cut biscuits out with top of drinking glass.

title: carrot-raisin salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Mix shredded carrots with combined ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: striped delight
directions: *Suggested Flavors:
Chocolate flavor pudding with graham cracker crumbs or butterscotch or lemon flavor pudding with gingersnap crumbs.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave the first 4 ingredients on High 2 minutes. Stir. Add the vanilla and nuts.
Stir.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cool on countertop.
May be stored in refrigerator.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Lightly cook broccoli.
Chop into small pieces (not grated). Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut into squares. Serves 12.
It is oh so good!

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs and undrained pineapple.
Mix only by hand.
Add bananas and nuts and mix again.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Let cool in pan 1 hour before removing to serving plate.

title: double cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix flour, mustard and red pepper.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in Swiss cheese, buttermilk and egg until dough forms.
Turn dough onto well-floured board; coat with flour.
Knead lightly 10 times. Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick; cut with floured 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Mix egg yolk and water; brush over biscuits.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into large pot.
Grate onion very fine and add to pot with celery seed, salt, margarine and water to completely cover potatoes.
Cook until tender, adding water as necessary to maintain level of broth.
Mash about half the potatoes and reduce rest to small pieces.
Cut up cheese into hot potatoes and broth.
Stir carefully until cheese has melted, then add milk.
Simmer over low heat until desired consistency.

title: chocolate rum souffle
directions: Soak macaroons in the rum.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate with water and 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Mix well.
Remove the chocolate from heat and add the egg yolks one at a time.
Let mixture cool.
Beat egg whites, adding 1 tablespoon sugar to make them more dense.
Fold into chocolate mixture gently.
Line bottom and sides of an oiled 7 1/2 or 8-inch spring-form pan with split ladyfingers.
Add half of the chocolate and then the layer of soaked macaroons.
Add the remaining chocolate mixture.
Top with remaining ladyfingers and cool for at least 6 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and apple.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and toss together.
Mix celery with mayonnaise and add to chicken and apple mixture.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce or eat as is. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: grated potato casserole
directions: Place milk, eggs, salt, pepper, cheese, butter or margarine, onion and cubed potatoes in blender container.
Blend on high speed, just until potatoes are grated.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: my favorite tuna fish sandwich
directions: Put tuna in a medium mixing bowl.
Add enough Miracle Whip to make it look creamy or to your taste.
Cut up pickles and put them in (I like lots of pickles).
Stir it all up and put it on the bread or eat with crackers.

title: texas style cornbread
directions: Grease large pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pie crust(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Sift into a bowl flour and salt.
Mix oil and milk.
Add all at once to the flour and stir until mixed,
Using the hands, form the mixture into a smooth ball.
Roll the dough between 2 sheets of wax paper until it is a circle about 11-inches in diameter. Remove one sheet of wax paper.
Turn the crust into a 9-inch pan. Remove wax paper.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes or until browned.
If the crust is to be baked with a filling, follow the cooking directions for the filling.
Double the recipe for a double crusted pie.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix meats together thoroughly.
Soak bread in cream about 5 minutes.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Mix meats, crumb mixture, onion, egg, parsley, salt, pepper, ginger and nutmeg until well combined.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown meat balls in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove from skillet.

title: true texas baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a large baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Cover top with crisp, crumbled bacon.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Mix together and cook over low fire for 1 hour or 1/2 hour.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease sides and bottom of a 10-inch deep-dish pie pan. In a medium mixing bowl, mix together flour, salt, baking powder and pudding mix. Mix in butter, egg and milk. Beat for 2 minutes. Pour mixture into pie pan. Arrange the peach slices on top of the pudding mixture. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach syrup. Beat for 2 minutes. Spoon mixture over peaches to within 1-inch of pan edge.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup milk.
Combine chocolate, butter, remaining milk, sugar, salt and vanilla in a double boiler.
Heat to the boiling point.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook 8 minutes. Let cool and pour into a baked pie shell.
To serve, top with whipped cream.

title: spice nut cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add shortening, brown sugar and buttermilk.
Mix until all flour is moistened.
Beat 2 minutes; add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes more; stir in nuts.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Frost with Orange Butter Frosting.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Add noodles to boiling water.
Boil according to instructions. Dice onion and saute in butter.
Add soup, milk, tuna, salt and pepper to onion.
Cook together for about 5 minutes; do not boil. Drain noodles.
Add tuna mixture to noodles and stir until combined.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until brown.

title: vegetables tossed in olive butter
directions: Mix vegetables and steam until tender.
Transfer to a bowl. Toss with Olive Butter.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: light strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and strawberries.
Bring to hard boil. Remove from stove and add Jello.
Cool.
Whip milk and add to mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Add a few drops of red food coloring if desired.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix
flour, margarine and pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9
x 13-inch
pan.
Bake
for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese,
powdered
sugar and 8-ounces Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk.
Spread over that layer. Top
with
another	8-ounces of Cool Whip and sprinkle chopped pecans on top; chill thoroughly.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges (use juice as a beverage). Combine pineapple, oranges, banana, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and almonds. Fold in yogurt. Chill. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Cut one pita bread in half.
Spread on ingredients (sauce, cheese, etc.).
Spray a cooking sheet with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: spray and wash
directions: Mix together and put into a spray bottle.
Use for removing stains before washing clothes.
Apply just before placing in wash. Be sure to always check for colorfastness on colored garments.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Steam carrots, broccoli, cauliflower and yellow squash until tender.
Drain.
To vegetables, add cream of celery soup.
Season with Italian seasoning.
In baking dish, build layers of noodles, vegetables and grated Mozzarella and Ricotta cheese.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is bubbly and brown.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Stir.
Line bottom of 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan with 2 cups corn chips.
Crush remaining chips and set aside.
Spoon meat mixture over corn chips.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with beans and spoon over meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and crushed chips.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: kayla's secret muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Add yogurt, mix at medium speed.
Mix in flour, salt, soda and poppy seed.
Put in muffin tins.
Bake at 400° approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 14 muffins.

title: baked chicken in sour cream
directions: Place chicken in greased flat 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, broth, water chestnuts and almonds.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs which have been tossed in oleo.
Bake at 375° until crackers are browned.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease baking dish.
Add crushed pineapple, pie filling, yellow cake mix and nuts in layers.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red punch
directions: Mix together; add water.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: sausage strata
directions: Put croutons in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan; top with cheese. Cook sausage in skillet until brown.
Drain on paper towels. Place sausage over cheese.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar until well blended.
Cool.
Stir in egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Then stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cut into bars or squares while still warm.

title: frosty pineapple punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a punch bowl.
Just before serving, spoon sherbet into punch bowl by heaping tablespoonfuls; stir gently.
Serve immediately.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: white drop cookies
directions: Beat egg(s), add sugar and shortening and stir well.
Add soda to your sour milk, then add to other ingredients.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt, then add vanilla.
Finally add chips and walnuts (optional) and stir together thoroughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: dill pickles
directions: Select fresh even cucumbers.
Wash and cut ends off.
Place dill in jar and clove of garlic.
(If you wish you can use hot peppers.)
Pack in sterilized jars.
Add 3 level teaspoons of salt in each jar.
Boil 1 quart vinegar and 3 quarts water.
Pour hot over pickles and seal.
Put in cold packer, starting with cold water.
When water comes to a boil, remove jars.
Let stand 4 weeks before eating.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Cool.
In separate bowl, chop the lettuce, onion and tomatoes.
Add ground beef.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Before serving, add cheese, dressing and crushed Fritos.

title: easy refrigerator roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, shortening, beaten egg, salt and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Place dough in greased bowl, then turn greased side up.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until ready to use.
Dough can be kept up to 4 days in refrigerator at 45° or below; keep covered.

title: nuts over turkey
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds. Bake at
350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 3 cups.
Has 300 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: country butter
directions: Note:
Have oleo and cream cheese at room temperature (soft).

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.
(When storing, keep cloves with beets in juice to keep flavor.
Lasts forever!)

title: continental round steaks
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:
In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook bacon until light brown.
Push bacon to one side of skillet.

title: h and j pizza
directions: Mix yeast and water together. Set aside.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together.
Combine both mixtures. Turn dough on floured board.
Knead. Spread on greased pizza pan.
Let stand 15 minutes. Spread spaghetti sauce on dough, then add cooked hamburger meat, mushrooms, cheese, onions, pepper or whatever you like. Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes. Eat and enjoy.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Prepare salad 1 hour before using and refrigerate.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and rinse with cold water. Add ham and remaining ingredients. Toss well. Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: oreo dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip. Mix milk and pudding.
When thick, fold into Cool Whip mixture. Put 1/2 of crumbled Oreos in bowl; layer pudding mixture and top with layer of Oreo crumbs.

title: potatoes deluxe i
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine in baking dish in slow oven.
Mix potatoes, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Put on top and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet and sour tofu and vegies
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons of water; add 1/4 cup pineapple juice, 1/4 cup water, vinegar, honey, soy sauce, ginger, and pepper; set aside.
Heat oil in a wok or large skillet on high heat.
Add onion and stir until strong smell starts to go away. Add carrot and stir a little more.
Add tofu and stir until lightly browned.
Add green pepper and salt.
Stir a minute more, then reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered.
Colorful, rich and juicy with a Chinese flavor.
A meal in itself with rice or chow mein noodles.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13 pan according to directions on box.
When done, poke holes in cake.
While cake is baking, combine pineapple and sugar and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cake while hot.
Let cake cool, then prepare instant pudding according to directions on box.
Spread pudding over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cheese and flour.
Place apples in a 2-quart dish.
Spread batter over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook the roast with the dried onion soup and Italian seasoning for 12 hours in crock-pot on low.
Cool and slice or shred meat. Save drippings.
To drippings, add the remaining ingredients. Simmer until ready to serve.

title: monastery lentil soup
directions: Saute oil, onions and carrots for 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients to one pot and cook for 45 minutes.
Add sherry at end.
Serve with Swiss cheese.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and spread on greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: saucy asparagus
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine soup and milk. Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Add asparagus.
Cover; cook over low heat 10 minutes or until asparagus is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired. Makes 8 servings.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Cook time:
15 minutes.

title: zombie
directions: Build in bucket glass with crushed ice.
Float rum.
Garnish with red cherry and orange slice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Top with French fried onions last 10 minutes.

title: yogurt pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir lemon rind, vanilla and yogurt into batter. Pour batter into
a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. (I just spray with Pam, no flour.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on a rack.
Sprinkle cake with powdered sugar, if desired.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: Saute beef and onion in a deep skillet.
Pour off fat, then add tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add 2 beaten eggs to cottage cheese, salt and oregano.
Place cooked noodles at the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, alternating the meat and egg and cottage cheese mixture.
Cover with half of the Mozzarella cheese, then a layer of noodles and repeat.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set about 15 minutes before serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together and set aside while preparing dressing.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, water chestnuts, cream of chicken soup, onion, and mayonnaise (or sour cream) together. Place in a 9 X 13 glass baking dish. Melt butter and mix with crumbled Ritz crackers. Spread crackers over top of casserole. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix jello and cold water; set for a couple minutes and add 1/4 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Add all ingredients.
Chill!

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve with cornbread.

title: chicken pie
directions: In fry pan cook chicken with olive oil.
Add diced carrots and broccoli.
Take a 9 inch pie pan and place a bottom crust.
In bowl mix soup with 1/2 c. milk.
In pie pan add your chicken, broccoli and carrots, potatoes.
Pour soup over ingredients.
Put top on pie.
Preheat over 350°.
Cook pie in oven until golden brown or approximately 1 hour.
tags: Cream of Campbell's Soup of your liking

title: cheese quiche
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, prepare pie crust mix as label directs for 1 crust pie; use to line 9-inch pie plate. Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl, with wire whisk or fork, mix eggs, half and half, salt and pepper until well blended. Sprinkle shredded cheese in pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake quiche 15 minutes, turn oven control to 325° and bake for 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center of quiche comes out clean.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: favorite baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble, reserving drippings.
Set bacon aside.
Saute onion, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard in a greased 1-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: baked chicken coating
directions: Brush chicken with oil and coat with this coating.
Bake until done.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening, beating in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flours together; add milk and vanilla.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and drain fat.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce and the taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Line bottom of 2-quart flat casserole with 2 cups corn chips.
Crush the remaining chips and set aside.
Spoon meat mixture over corn chips in dish.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and the refried beans. Spread over meat.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and crushed corn chips.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Serves 5.

title: broccoli nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain. Add soup, mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix well. Add eggs and onion.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and top with crumbs. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: joyce's fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour, soda, allspice and milk.
Fold in candied fruit, nuts and raisins. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add salt and soda.
Stir well.
Add flour and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven when light brown.

title: broccoli & cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Dehead broccoli and cauliflower.
Put in a 3-quart pot with enough water to cover vegetables.
Cover and steam until done. Drain.
Add 1 to 1-1/2 quarts of milk and 1/2 loaf of Velveeta cheese.
Cover.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: homestyle pot pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with 1 crust; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour filling in pie crust. Top with second crust. Seal and crimp edges. Slit top of crust to vent and bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, syrup and butter and mix well. Add vanilla; add peanuts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is firm and brown.
Pie may be soft when shaken gently but will firm as it cools.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger together; drain grease off.
Put in a bowl while warm; mix Cheez Whiz.
Put on party rye bread (rye bread) and broil until bread is lightly brown and crisp.
Watch close.

title: spiced apple loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a medium bowl, mix together flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, using a wooden spoon or an electric mixer set on medium speed, beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in the apples.
Stir flour mixture into the apple mixture until the dry ingredients are just moistened.
Spoon batter into the prepared pan.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 1 hour. Transfer the pan to a wire rack to cool for 10 minutes.
Turn the cake out onto the rack to cool completely.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender, drain.
Stir in apples, sauerkraut, water, brown sugar and caraway seeds.
Transfer to a 2 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Make 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and syrup; mix well.
Add eggs, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Lower temperature to 300° and cook for 35 minutes longer.

title: ri's easy salisbury steak
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients, except peas and gravy, and shape into 2 loaves.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Place loaves in dish, lightly spray top with Pam to help brown nicely and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Add gravy and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Then add peas to gravy and steak.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk custard pie(my mother's recipe)
directions: Beat egg yolks, butter and sugar.
Add flour and buttermilk. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add extract. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: bbq rice
directions: Pour rice
in
a large baking dish.
Add soup and mushrooms and
stir
to mix.	Place 1 stick of margarine in center of dish. Bake
in
preheated oven at 400° for approximately 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all but bread cubes and raisins.
Add bread cubes and raisins.
Pour into well oiled baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells florentine
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Pour marinara sauce into saucepan and heat.
Spoon 1 cup of sauce into bottom of a large roasting pan or 1/2 cup sauce into each of two 2-quart baking pans.
Reserve remaining sauce; keep warm.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine the 1 tablespoon flour and the salt; coat meat.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet; add meat and brown quickly on both sides.
Add mushrooms, onion, and garlic; cook till crisp-tender, 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove meat and mushrooms from pan. Add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings.
Blend in the 3 tablespoons flour.
Add tomato paste; stir in beef stock.
Cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Return browned meat and mushrooms to skillet.
Stir in sour cream and wine; cook slowly until hot; do not boil.
Serve over noodles. Serves 4 or 5.

title: orange raisin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Beat egg whites in small bowl; stir in milk, juice, oil and peel. Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in cereal. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns and combine in a large bowl with melted butter, salt and pepper.
Add onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Blend ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix 1/4 cup melted butter with corn flakes. Sprinkle crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french pea soup
directions: Wash peas and put in 6-quart pot.
Add 6 cups water and 2 onions.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes.
Add carrots and celery. Cook for an additional 30 minutes on low heat, continuing to be sure it remains boiling.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: casserole sauce mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in an airtight container and keep in refrigerator.
This recipe makes 3 cups mix (equivalent of nine 10 1/2 ounce cans of condensed cream soup).

title: old-time tea cakes
directions: Break eggs into mixing bowl.
Add margarine, molasses, sugar, nutmeg and baking soda.
Cream thoroughly.
Work in flour. Transfer dough to a well floured board and knead until it is pliable.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° until light brown.
Yields 3 dozen tea cakes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine spices in a spice bag. Add to the other ingredients in a large pan on stove or use large coffeepot.
Simmer.

title: cocoa delight cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add Crisco and first amount of milk called for.
Beat with mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, rest of milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Spread batter in 2 well greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook until blended and slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Add cream.
Beat until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar gradually until right consistency to spread.

title: party casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; add Ragu sauce and heat to boiling point. Beat cream cheese; add cottage cheese, sour cream and olives and mix.
In a 3-quart casserole, layer 1/2 beef mixture, 1/2 noodles, cheese mixture, remaining noodles and top with remaining beef mixture.
Bake.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: Combine everything in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until pasta is tender.

title: banana nut roll
directions: Lightly grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Line bottom with waxed paper; set aside.

title: instant lemon pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Chill and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put 5 pats of butter, brown sugar sprinkles and pecans in the bottom of pan. Quarter biscuits and roll in white sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Melt butter and brown sugar over low heat.
Add cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes; then 350 degrees of 20 minutes or until biscuits are done in center.

title: venison roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put roast in roasting pan.
Add water, tenderizer and cover.
Cook for 1 hour.
Peel potatoes and cut in half.
Cut celery in half.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and return to oven for 1 more hour.
At end of baking time, remove from oven.
Place roast on platter and surround with veggies.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Sprinkle flour on cheese.
Pour on butter.
Add salt and red pepper.
Add Rice Krispies.
Knead by hand.
Roll into marble sized balls and bake on ungreased sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in frying pan.
Salt and pepper pork chops.
Brown pork chops in pan until braised on both sides but not until done.
Remove from frypan and put aside.
Melt rest of butter in frypan.
Add rice and brown.
Add consomme, onion soup and mushrooms.
Bring to a slight boil.
Pour into a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with pork chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Combine five ingredients in food processor; process until blended and cheese is fine as you want it.
Add pimiento; process just to blend.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Makes 3 cups.

title: irish coffee
directions: Fill a stemmed glass with hot water, then empty glass.
Refill with boiling water and empty again.
Fill the glass more than half full with the coffee and sugar to taste.
Stir and add whiskey. Spoon on whipped cream and drink hot coffee through cool cream.

title: stuffed mandarin ham
directions: Prepare stuffing and let stand 2 minutes.
Add oranges to stuffing.
Place 1/4 stuffing in each ham slice.
Roll ham and place each one, seam down, in a baking dish.
Spoon remaining stuffing around ham slices.
Spoon marmalade over all.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick potato salad
directions: Cut slightly cooked potatoes into 1 inch cubes.
In large bowl combine potatoes, onions and salad dressing.
Toss gently. Dust with paprika.
Garnish with chives and bacon bits.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: baked potatoes and onions
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Put into shallow baking pan and mix oil into potatoes.
Pour dry soup mix over potatoes and mix well. Bake in oven at 350° or until done.

title: fruit soup(servings:  8)
directions: In food processor, blend strawberries until smooth; pour into saucepan.
Add water, sugar, tapioca and salt; let stand 5 minutes.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Chill; add orange sections just before serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In large pan, saute onions, bell pepper, shallots, celery and garlic in oil until tender.
In small skillet, make roux of 1/4 cup oil and 1/4 cup flour and brown; add to onion mixture.
Add to onion mixture the tomato sauce, tomato paste, water and all seasonings, except parsley and lemon juice.
Simmer 45 minutes. Add shrimp, lemon juice and parsley.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Serve over rice.
Serves 10.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Add 4 cups of boiling water to powdered Jell-O.
Stir with wooden spoon until completely dissolved.
In place of cold water, slowly add partially softened vanilla ice cream to Jell-O mixture in pan.
Stir until completely melted.
Refrigerate in 10 x 13-inch pan until set (approximately 2 to 3 hours). Cut into squares.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: easy hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into squares.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Soak potatoes in water.
Then shake well in bag, coating well.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Place potatoes in dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn once during baking.

title: cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and cheese in a large bowl.
Mix until a soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Mix the butter and garlic powder in a small bowl.
Brush the butter mixture over the warm biscuits.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs, pumpkin and oil. Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes on a large cookie sheet.

title: fast rolls
directions: Beat well; cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Stir and spoon into muffin cups.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: passion-orange pudding jello
directions: Dissolve orange
jello	in boiling water.
Add passion-orange juice,
then add evaporated milk.
Whip all ingredients together. Let stand for 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Stir in oatmeal.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: red rolled enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil in a small frying pan until soft, approximately 2 to 3 seconds on each side. Set aside. Place 1 tablespoon of sauce on each and stack. Brown ground beef and drain the fat off. Add one can sauce and simmer together for about 5 minutes or until the beef and sauce are well mixed. Fill tortillas with beef, 4 ounces cheese and olives. Roll and place into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Pour remaining sauce over the top and sprinkle the rest of the cheese and olives on top. Bake at 250° for 10 to 20 minutes until cheese is melted. Makes 5 to 6 servings, depending on how many enchiladas you can make with this recipe. Also great to reheat. You may use Monterey Jack and can use more or less if you like cheesy enchiladas.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a casserole dish place a layer of peeled, sliced potatoes. Spoon mushroom soup and cubed Spam.
Another layer potatoes, soup and Spam.
Fill up dish.
Add salt and pepper (to taste).
Mix one can water into mushroom soup can; mix.
Pour over potatoes, Spam and soup.
Add more water, enough to fill casserole dish up to top layer of potatoes.
Bake at 400° until potatoes are tender.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and celery in chicken broth to package directions.
Drain, add green pepper, onion and diced chicken to spaghetti.
Set aside.
Prepare cheese sauce, milk, flour and margarine in medium sized saucepan.
Cook until thick, stir constantly.
Add grated cheese and mushroom soup.
Mix cheese sauce into spaghetti mixture.
Pour into large oblong baking dish.
Top with margarine and cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in margarine, buttermilk, and molasses.
Put in unbeaten eggs and mix.
Beat by hand 20 strokes. Butter and flour a 9 x 9 x 5-inch glass pan, or 8 x 12-inch aluminum pan.
Pour in mixture and bake at 340° to 350° heat for 45 minutes.
The bigger the dish, the less heat.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a saucepan melt butter, oil, cocoa and water and bring to a boil.
Mix with flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Then add buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured sheet pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring to boil the white sugar and white syrup; add peanut butter and Special K cereal.
Spread on buttered 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet.
Melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Spread on top of mixture on sheet.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend together; drop from teaspoon onto wax paper. Let set for 1 hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Eggs:
We usually do 12 to 18, depends on size of group you are feeding or the size of your deviled egg dish.

title: linley's jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Let cool and add cream cheese.
Mash with a fork and stir together.
Then add pineapple and Cool Whip. Last, add 7-Up slowly.
Put into square Pyrex or plastic container.
Refrigerate.

title: black forest cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Empty cherries into a baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool for about 20 minutes.
Remove cake from pan, sitting right side up.
Cut all sides off cake.
Slice cake in half lengthwise.
Remove top layer carefully, a spatula will help.
Put bottom layer back in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cherries on bottom layer.
Replace top layer and spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti and rinse in hot water.
Add beaten eggs and butter; mix well.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Add Parmesan cheese and mushrooms.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over meat and top with Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: In large bowl, crumble beef.
Heat in microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High until beef is browned, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in sauce and water.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix for 5 minutes. Pour into a pint jar.
Serve on garden salad.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter until soft; beat in sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and sour cream, alternately to creamed mixture, starting and ending with flour. Add flavoring and beat until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake 1 1/2 hours until golden brown, top springs back when touched.
Cool on wire rack before turning out.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop popcorn; put into a large pan.
Mix sugar, syrup, water, vinegar and butter in saucepan; boil until it forms a firm ball in cold water.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir until all is covered. Use lots of butter or margarine on hands as you form balls.
Makes 12 large popcorn balls.

title: buttercream easter eggs
directions: Note:
Use 1/4 cup peanut butter in place of 1/4 cup margarine.

title: mom's favorite hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes to small pieces. Mix artichokes with rest of the ingredients.
Place in decorative baking dish in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: five hour oven stew
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients and let stand while preparing vegetables.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix creamed corn, whole kernel corn, and melted oleo.
Add Jiffy cornbread mix and sour cream.
Beat egg and add to this mixture.
Add softened Cheez Whiz.
Mix well. Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat, eggs, crumbs, onion, parsley flakes and Worcestershire sauce together.
Season to taste.
Shape into meatballs and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Drop into sauce and heat thoroughly.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Pour into skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and boiling.
Stir 1 minute.
Add meatballs and pineapple bits; heat thoroughly.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Press the liquid from the grated potatoes and discard. Combine grated potatoes with the mashed potatoes, egg yolk, salt and pepper. Shape into desired size pancakes and fry until brown and crisp on both sides.
The pancakes are often served with sauerbraten or other substantial meat dishes or as a luncheon dish together with applesauce.

title: marinated sirloin roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over roast.
Turn roast over in sauce and cover all sides.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in slow oven at 325°.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Make a well in dry ingredients. Add milk.
Roll out or pat down on a floured board and cut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: jiffy cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 3 cups flour, cake mix, yeast, salt and warm water.
Mix until smooth, add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead until smooth, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Roll dough into a 9 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough jelly-roll style, starting with the long end.
Slice the dough into 1-inch circles, place on greased cookie sheet.
