Place cut side down around edge of casserole pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are brown.
Take out; top with cheese and return to oven until melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon.
Add hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake until it bubbles (approximately 1 hour) at 350°.
Freezes well before baking for later use.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Beat egg yolks well, slowly adding sugar, then baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well. Beat whites until stiff peaks, fold into yolk mix.
Fold in crumbs and nuts.
Pour into two 9 or 8-inch pans, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and frost when cool.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in large mixing bowl.
In small saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar; mix well.
Add buttermilk with soda, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange peach jello salad
directions: Cook until thick.
Be sure and let cool and mix with one package of Dream Whip, prepared as directed.
Fold into cool mixture and spread on jello.

title: great creamed potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes.
Boil until tender; drain.
Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream until well blended.
Add hot potatoes, gradually beating until light and fluffy.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southwestern shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; cut in half.
Heat oil in nonstick pan over medium-high heat. Saute onion, cilantro and jalapeno for 5 minutes.	Stir in tomato sauce. Add shrimp and stir until shrimp turns pink. Serve over white rice. Serves 2.

title: puffed pancake with strawberries
directions: Mix eggs, milk, orange juice, sugar, flour and salt until blended (if using a mixer, batter may remain lumpy).
Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish in oven until it sizzles (don't let it brown).
Remove baking dish from oven and pour batter into it immediately.
Bake in middle of oven for 20 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Pancake falls quickly so serve immediately with warm Strawberry Sauce and sour cream.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown
meat and drain.
Add seasoning.
Mix with cheese until melted.
Spread over rye bread.
Broil slices on cookie sheet until golden brown.

title: golden glazed chicken
directions: In shallow baking dish, arrange chicken and brush with butter. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Baste once with pan drippings. Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes more, or until chicken is done.

title: indian black-eyed peas and potatoes
directions: In skillet heat oil.
Add mustard seed.
Cover and cook until seed begins to pop.
Remove from heat.
Remove lid, stir in cumin. Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until onion is tender but not brown.
Stir in undrained black-eyed peas, potatoes, ginger, turmeric and red pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Cut out center of bread and spoon in dip.
Slice fresh veggies and cut rest of bread into cubes.
Dip and enjoy!
(Best if made the day before.)

title: impossible spinach pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pie plate.
Mix spinach, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
About 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: apple walnut ring cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add gradually to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Batter will be stiff. Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to rack to cool.
Dribble confectioners sugar icing on top and sides, if desired.

title: chocolate sunshine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well.
Beat 3 minutes. Batter is very thin.
Bake 30 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°. Frost with your favorite white icing.
Serves 20 slices.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; toss.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce; add to chicken mixture, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Put into a 9-inch pie pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Set aside.
Cream together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into crust and bake 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add food coloring and gelatin.

title: mama's homecooking fried muskrat
directions: First, trap muskrat.
Then skin muskrat, then cut into 4 pieces.
Once this is completed, dip into egg and milk, then roll into flour, cracker meal, salt and pepper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, mushroom soup, cheese, mayonnaise, egg and onion together in baking dish.
Crumble cracker crumbs on top and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: festive chicken dip
directions: Place chicken in a small bowl. Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons lime juice, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Set aside.

title: fruit yogurt salad
directions: Cook liquids and cornstarch until thick, cool.
Combine yogurt, sugar and vanilla and mix with cooled mixture.
Stir in fruit and chill.
Be creative and add different kinds of fruits.

title: bread machine bread
directions: Add ingredients to the bread pan in the order listed, measuring carefully and using a knife to scrape off the excess. Bake as directed by the directions on the bread machine. Makes 1 1/2 lb. loaf.
(You may also use the dough setting on your machine and when the dough is ready, form it into dinner rolls. Let them rise until doubled in size, then bake at 375° until brown.)

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, add ingredients in order, starting with rice.
Salt, pepper and flour chicken and dip each piece in liquid shortening.
Put chicken into casserole mixture, cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and put in an 11 x 13 baking dish. Top with 1 package of Pillsbury pie crust from the dairy section. I use a small biscuit cutter and lap it but it will still be vented. Bake at 350° to 375° about 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: good rich yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1 teaspoon sugar in lukewarm water.
Sift flour with remaining sugar and salt; add eggs, milk, shortening and cooled yeast.
Mix. Turn dough onto floured board and knead.
Pinch off and roll into golf ball size balls; place in greased muffin pans.
Let rise (covered with light cloth).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yields about 36 rolls.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Have icing ready when the cake is done.

title: pumpkin bars(microwave)
directions: Blend oil, eggs, sugar and pumpkin together in large mixing bowl.
Measure flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and nutmeg into 1-quart measure.
Mix together lightly with fork.
Stir into pumpkin mixture.
Divide butter equally into two 8 x 8-inch glass pans.
One at a time, cover with plastic wrap. Microwave 5 minutes and 30 seconds to 11 to 13 minutes on High, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand until thoroughly cooled.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: manicotti casserole
directions: Cook manicotti noodles as directed on package. Let cool. Stuff with grated cheeses. Place manicotti in dish; cover with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is hot.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to a boil.
Add peanuts, stirring constantly.
Cook until peanuts start popping.
Remove from heat and add soda and stir quickly until well mixed.
Pour in greased pan.
Let cool and break into desired pieces.

title: special scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt half of butter in large skillet; add potatoes and stir until coated.
Mix other ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt other half of butter and stir in corn flakes. Spread over top of potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For a one dish meal, add chunks of chicken or ham.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions, sweet and hot peppers, sugar and salt.
Cook gently 45 minutes.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag; add them to tomato mixture.
Cook until very thick, about 45 minutes.
As mixture thickens, stir often to prevent sticking. Add vinegar and cook slowly until thick as desired.
Pour boiling hot into jars, leaving 1/8-inch space and seal.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Add all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put in muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix till smooth.
Pour into 3 loaf pans, greased and floured and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spray a large cookie sheet or large pizza pan with Pam. Spread crescent rolls on sheet to make a crust.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Ranch dressing and Miracle Whip.
Spread on crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on top of crust and cover with shredded cheese/cheeses.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple into pan.
Place cherries over pineapple. Dump cake mix evenly over filling.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: ann's cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat, celery, onion and salt.
In a kettle, cook cabbage for 5 minutes.
After it starts boiling, drain and add meat mixture.
Then add rice and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Put in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
You may substitute bell pepper for celery and chicken soup for mushroom if you desire.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, chicken and pineapple together well.
Be sure to drain chicken and pineapple well.
Roll in crushed pecans.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to full boil in medium saucepan on medium-high heat. Stir in rice. Cover. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Add Velveeta. Stir until Velveeta is melted.

title: cream of corn and crabmeat soup
directions: In a large saucepot, add Wesson oil, corn, onion, celery and red pepper. Let saute until tender for 20 minutes.

title: bonnymill baked eggs
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into an oiled 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until mixture is set and top is golden, about 45 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars until light.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet; set aside.
Layer vegetables in skillet:
carrots, onion, celery, zucchini and green peas.
Top off with cabbage; season and dot with butter.
Cover tightly with lid; bring to boil.
Let simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, until vegetables are done.
Best when the vegetables are still slightly crisp.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken and soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13 covered with foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: squash pie (coconut flavor)(tastes just like coconut pie)
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Heat together in a pan until red hots are completely dissolved.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Set aside.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate flavored chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 370° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt. Set aside.
Bring cream, vanilla, butter, cocoa and water to a boil and pour over dry mixture. Add eggs and soda.
Mix well. Bake in a greased and floured sheet at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 1-inch balls.
Press flat on greased cookie sheet with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hot antipasto casserole
directions: Boil artichoke hearts for 5 minutes.
Drain and quarter.
Mix all ingredients, except olives.
Slice olives.
Place on top. Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes at 450° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: day before salad(serves 10)
directions: Layer lettuce and chopped vegetables, saving enough lettuce for top layer.
Layer the peas and last layer of lettuce.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Add thick layer of Parmesan cheese and refrigerate a day or two. Crumble 1/2 pound of cooked crisp bacon and spread on top.
Looks pretty in deep glass bowl.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place ground meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Put green beans on top of meat.
Pour Tater Tots on top of beans.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 10 minutes.

title: hello dollies(makes 24 squares)
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle the wafers over top evenly.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts on top.
Pour the milk over all and bake at 350° for thirty minutes. Cut into squares while warm.
(I doubled the recipe.)

title: rich yeast rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water; stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add about half the flour; add the beaten eggs and beat well.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough; mix thoroughly.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead about 10 minutes or until smooth and satiny.

title: muscadine dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Mix with muscadine hot sauce.
Serve with round (small) tortillas chips.

title: * butterscotch no bake cookies *
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter together in top of double boiler.
Add cereal.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in potato chips and chopped nuts.
Add flour.
Blend well.
Form into small balls with hands.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with floured glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: damn good pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and butter and put in saucepan.
Cook on low heat until butter melts.
Add coconut and pineapple.
Stir all together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until pie is golden brown.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as on box.
When warm, poke holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk and caramel over holes.
Refrigerate overnight. Pour Cool Whip over top and top with Heath bits.

title: biscuit dough(very light; for obstorte, roll, cakes and cheesecake.)
directions: Sift flour 4 times.
Beat egg yolks until thick and creamy, lemon colored.
Add water; continue beating until very thick. Gradually beat in sugar, then extract.
Fold in flour, a little at a time.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until they form moist, glossy peaks.
Fold in egg yolk mixture.
Bake in angel food pan in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour. Invert 15 minutes.
Use whatever size pan is needed for: obstorte, cake, cheesecake, etc.
Fill with apricot jam.
Top with cream filling.
Decorate with cake decorator.

title: blue devil salad
directions: In a 2-quart dish, dissolve gelatin in water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, nuts and sugar.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Chill.

title: crustless cheesecake
directions: Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In Dutch oven heat water and bouillon until dissolved.
Add broccoli; cover and cook until broccoli is tender.
Add milk, cheese and dash of pepper.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted. Combine 1/4 cup flour with 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir into broccoli mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caribbean pumpkin soup
directions: Coat a medium saucepan with cooking spray; heat over medium heat. Add onion and bell pepper and saute about 5 minutes. Stir in garlic and cumin and cook 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes to blend flavors.

title: german kuchen
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, beaten eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Reserve 1 cup batter for top.
After spreading the portion of batter in bottom of pan, spoon pie filling on batter.
Drop the rest of the batter on top of filling, not completely covering it.
When baked, fruit will ooze up through batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 325° if using glass dish.

title: dried fruit pie
directions: Put fruit in bottom of pie shell. Beat egg yolks. Add milk. Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add sugar mixture and butter to beaten egg
yolks, then add vanilla flavoring.
Pour over fruit. Bake at 325° until set.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Set aside.
Cook wild rice separately; set aside.
Saute onion in butter; add soup, mushrooms, milk and flour and heat until well blended and hot. Make layers of rice, chicken, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook beans and barley according to package directions in large pot with onion, pepper and celery.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato paste and remaining ingredients.
Add beans and simmer 45 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo and stir into stuffing.
Put 1/2 of this into casserole.
Then put chicken over this.
Pour broth over this. Mix sour cream and soup
togther,
then put over chicken.
Top with rest of stuffing.
Spoon
a little broth over all.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: harvest fruit bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in medium bowl; set aside, stirring occasionally.
In large bowl beat together margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, oats and 1/2 teaspoon apple pie spice; mix until crumbly.
Save 3/4 cup mixture for topping. Press rest into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: creamy crunchy chicken "n" rice bake
directions: Combine rice and cheese.
Mix well. Add chicken, peas and half of the onions. Mix lightly. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: little smokies in sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Smokies.
Cook on stove top until thick.
Add Smokies.
Serve warm.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix the flour and salt.
Cut in the shortening with knives. Combine lightly only until the mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle water over the mixture.
Mix lightly with a fork, using only enough water so that the pastry will hold together when pressed gently into a ball.
Makes enough for a 9-inch 2-crust pie.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic until brown and tender.
Combine beans, oregano, chili powder, chiles, tomato sauce and water in separate saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.

title: favorite fishermans chowder
directions: Cut fillets into 2 to 3 pieces.
In heavy skillet, saute onions in 1/4 cup butter until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Add potatoes, salt, pepper and boiling water.
Arrange fish fillets on top.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add scalded milk, light cream and 3 tablespoons butter.
Heat until very hot.
Slice tomato and float on top of chowder.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients with little hands.
Store in Ziploc bag. Add food coloring for more fun.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put graham crackers on top.
Put chips on top of crumbs.
Put coconut on top of chips.
Put pecans on top of coconut.
Spread Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add 1 cup boiling water. Stir together.
Knead mixture until it forms a soft dough.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli and dried onion in salted water. Before totally cooked, add undiluted soup, butter and milk. Simmer a little while. Cut cheese into chunks and let melt in soup. Keep stirring as it tends to stick. Serves about 8.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Cream cheese, softened.
Add butter, chicken, mushrooms and Lawry's seasoning.
Flatten rolls with a rolling pin; put 1/8 of chicken mixture on roll.
Roll to form from narrow end.
Dip in melted butter and roll into walnuts, then in bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, until done.
Thicken chicken broth and use as a side dish to pour over chicken.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat the eggs until they are creamy.
Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add to the eggs, a small amount at a time.
Add liquids slowly in the order they are listed.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain thoroughly.
Add cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, red pepper, salt, pepper and tomatoes; heat through. Cover bottom and sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Pour beef mixture over tortillas.
Place a layer of tortillas over meat mixture and set aside.

title: marinated chuck
directions: Mix first three ingredients together first (so mustard doesn't clump).
Mix rest.
Pour over chuck steaks or Spencer steaks. Marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Barbecue or broil.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in butter in skillet.
Mix beef broth bouillon soup, French onion soup and browned rice in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Excellent with smothered quail.
I usually double this recipe.

title: vegetable balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, until thick.
Shape into balls.
Place into hot oil to fry.
Drain and serve warm.

title: yummy deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 15 minutes.
Cool off and peel.
Slice in half. Place yolks in a bowl.
Mash with a fork until smooth.
Add salad dressing, sweet relish, mustard and sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon up and place in center of each egg half.
Sprinkle with paprika and refrigerate.

title: dark chocolate drop cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a double boiler.
Cream egg and chocolate mixture with sugar and salt.
Beat until the mixture is light and smooth, then add vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder. Add the flour and baking powder alternately with the milk into the creamed mixture.
Work in the nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: balcom's beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 3-quart covered casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease square brownie pan.
Dump cherry filling in pan; add cake mix and pour melted margarine over top. Spread pecans on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: luby's pan-grilled fish(lo-fat)
directions: Combine water, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl. In a separate bowl, mix flour, paprika and seasoned salt. Preheat electric skillet to 325° of place a heavy skillet on the stove and preheat on medium-high. Dip fish fillets in liquid mixture and then place in flour mixture, covering completely. Shake off excess flour and place fillets, meat side down, in greased preheated pan. Cook 6 to 7 minutes, depending on the thickness, then turn over and cook until firm to touch (about 6 minutes more).
Garnish each with a sprig of parsley and a lemon twist.
Serves 6.

title: goulash
directions: In a large pot, cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until tender.
Season ground beef with salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes, catsup, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Let simmer about 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add water.
Bring to a full boil.
Add macaroni.
Cook until macaroni is tender.
Stir often to prevent macaroni from sticking.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and reserve syrup, make up to 1 c.

with water. Bring to a boil, dissolve the gelatin in the hot liquid and allow to cool. Gently stir in ginger ale, chill until partially set. Whip the cranberry sauce, stir in pineapple and fold in the gelatin. Turn into a mold and chill until firm. Blend together the Cool Whip and cream cheese, spread over the gelatin mold, sprinkle with pecans.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and break or tear into bite size pieces; discard the skin.
Dice celery ribs into small pieces.
Peel and cut oranges into bite size pieces.
Take 2 quarts of water and add the lemon juice.
Cut up apples into bite size pieces and let soak in water-lemon mixture.
(This prevents apples from turning brown.) Add drained apples, chicken, oranges, almonds, mayonnaise and sugar together in a bowl and mix together.
You may add more mayonnaise and sugar to your own taste.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to boiling.
Stir in Bisquick. Stir about 1 minute or until forms a ball. Remove from heat. Beat in eggs until smooth.
Mix in cheese and Italian seasoning. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until puffed and light golden brown.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator until served.

title: real holland pancakes(eierpannekoeken)
directions: Slice bread an hour or two before you make the French toast, if you can, so that it will dry out.
Put oven on low (unless intending to serve as soon as cooked).
Beat eggs with milk and stir in vanilla, honey, cinnamon, nutmeg, optional orange flower water and salt.
Heat butter in a large, heavy frying pan over low heat.
Dip bread slices into batter on both sides.
They should be saturated but not so soggy that they will fall apart.
Place in frying pan and continue dipping slices and adding them to pan (but don't overcrowd the pan).
Saute slowly, until the first side turns golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Then turn and saute on the other side until golden brown.
Place in oven on a baking sheet to keep warm if you aren't serving at once.
Serve with honey.

title: jackie's gorditas(jackie clotfelter)
directions: Combine masa, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add water slowly and knead to a stiff dough.
Cover dough and let sit for 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 6 portions and roll into balls.
Roll balls out to 1/4-inch thick.
Deep fry until puffed and browned. (They will be hollow.)
Cut off the end and stuff as you would a taco.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one is added.
Sift dry ingredients, including cocoa.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla, ending with dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(This makes a big cake.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 5
to	9
minutes
at 425° (hot oven); makes about 5 dozen with 2-inch cutter.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, melted margarine and sugar; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread mixture over cooled pretzels.
Prepare strawberry jello and 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries to jello.
Pour onto cheese mixture when slightly thickened.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in baking dish. Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 40 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 20 minutes or until brown.
Contains 242 calories, 15 fat and 78 cholesterol.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Form a ball.
Sprinkle or roll ball in Ranch mix.
Cover with pecans or bacon bits.

title: mom's crushed banana cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar
and
eggs.
Add bananas, mashed through a sieve.
Add
sour milk, in which you dissolve baking soda.
Lastly, add flour,
baking
powder and salt; beat well. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in a tube pan in moderate oven for 40 minutes.
May ice or glaze if desired.

title: diet orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello and hot water.
Add salad dressing; beat.
Stir in cottage cheese, oranges, pineapple and cherries.
Refrigerate until set.

title: orange creamsicle cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Bake cake as directed on box in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool slightly. Using a fork, poke holes 1-inch apart throughout.
Pour Jell-O over entire cake slowly.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: rainbow twirls
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
In a large bowl toss pasta, cheese, onions, radishes, olives and cucumbers.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Toss with the pasta and spread evenly. Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Cool cake 15 minutes. Punch holes in top with a fork.
Combine milk, sugar and coconut.
Bring to a boil and simmer one minute.
Spoon over cake. Cool cake completely.
Top with Cool Whip mixed with 1/2 cup coconut or sprinkle coconut across top.

title: glorious macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Saute onion, pimento and mushrooms in butter.
Combine macaroni, onion mixture and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together soups and sour cream.
Microwave onions on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add onions, potatoes and cheese to soup and sour cream mixture.
Add salt, pepper and onion powder.
Place in greased casserole.
Melt margarine and crumble Ritz crackers; mix with hands until all are buttery.
Sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle topping with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scones
directions: Scone dough must be handled minimally and quickly.
As soon as the soda makes contact with liquid the rising action has begun. The object is to get the scones into the oven quickly while the dough is still wobbling so the rising is not wasted.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix vanilla pudding mix in fruit cocktail, then add apple, cherries and bananas.

title: donna's lasagna
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef and sausage; drain excess fat.
Add pureed tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, 1 tablespoon parsley, basil, garlic and 1 teaspoon salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: lillie mae's cake
directions: Mix ingredients together adding only enough pineapple or applesauce to make cake.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tangy salsa shrimp and rice
directions: In bowl, mix shrimp and salsa.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Cook rice and add chilies, scallions, salt and pepper. Mix well. Skewer salsa-coated shrimp; broil or grill.
Place on rice.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Oil bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all the ingredients.
Pour into casserole; top with bacon strips, very thin ones.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ultimate onion
directions: Mix the cornstarch, flour and seasonings until well blended. Add beer; mix well.
Cut about 3/4-inch off top of onion; peel onion.
Cut onion into 12 to 16 vertical wedges, but do not cut through bottom (root end).
Remove about 1 inch of "petals" from center of onion.
Dip cut onion in Seasoned Flour and remove excess by shaking; dip in batter and remove excess by gently shaking. Separate "petals" to coat thoroughly with batter.
Mix batter after standing to blend ingredients.
Gently place in fryer basket and deep fry at 375° to 400° for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn over and fry 1 to 1 1/2 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Place onion upright in shallow bowl and remove center core with circular cutter on apple corer.
Serve hot with Creamy Chili Sauce.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with reserved coconut.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease cookie sheet.
Place shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla in mixing bowl and beat thoroughly.
Sift together salt, flour and soda and add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in oats and drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
If you wish, you may also add 1/3 cup chopped nuts, raisins or shredded coconut to the batter.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until slightly brown at the edges.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sweet spice pickles
directions: *The oils can be purchased at a drugstore if not found at grocery store.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape dough into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, spinach, Parmesan cheese and egg until well blended.
Layer 1 cup sauce, 3 noodles, 1 cup Ricotta cheese mixture and part of Mozzarella cheese in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes; remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: little debbie cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and spices.
Add rest of ingredients and roll into small balls.
Flatten on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Fill with filling.

title: bacon cheese fries
directions: Cook French fries according to package directions. Place fries on a broiler proof dish or platter. Sprinkle with cheese, onions and bacon. Broil for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with Ranch dressing. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine and pour over meatballs. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican salad
directions: In large shallow baking pan, put 1 layer corn chips (not too thick, as it dries out), 1 layer rice and 1 layer hamburger mixture (hamburger, onion, tomato sauce and chili seasoning).
Sprinkle with grated cheese (Cheddar).
Put in oven to melt cheese.
On top, put 1 layer shredded lettuce and 1 layer cherry tomatoes (or cut up whole tomatoes).

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion lightly in skillet, stirring until beef is crumbly; drain well. Layer ground beef mixture, green beans and Tater Tots in 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine soup and milk in bowl, beating well. Pour over layers. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until brown.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can Durkee French fried onions around and under chicken.
Combine chicken broth and Italian seasoning and pour the mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake another 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt butter and brown steak.
Add onions and peppers to meat and add all other ingredients except cornstarch.
Cook on low heat 10 to 15 minutes and then thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: the ten minutes, no fuss, healthy lunch
directions: In medium bowl, combine the chickpeas, tomatoes, onion and tuna.
Mix olive oil, vinegar and pepper until blended.
Pour over chickpeas-tuna mixture.
Toss.
Serve with bread.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: melrose's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients good.
Roll into a ball, then roll in toasted pecans or almonds.
Can double ingredients for a larger cheese ball.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut up chicken in cubes.
In pan, mix chicken noodle soup (starter) and frozen vegetables (stewed vegetables are best).
Add bouillon cubes, dissolved in water.
Cook all day in crock-pot. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.

title: pepper sauce
directions: Bring vinegar to boil.
Put hot peppers in sterilized jars; pour vinegar over peppers and seal jars.
Can put in onions and tomatoes also.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix into boiling milk.
Cook a few minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate with milk over low heat; stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
In large bowl, beat butter with peanut butter and sugar until blended.
Stir in flour and oats until combined.
Measure out 1 cup and set aside. Press remaining oat mixture into pan.
Spread chocolate over. Crumble reserved 1 cup of oat mixture over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mrs. davie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts; mix well. Shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly or overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick; bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Place bread in bottom of dish, then sprinkle cheese and sausage over it.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over cheese and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "bonnie's" sweet potato gook
directions: Drain yams.
Add pineapple, white sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Mash until creamy; spread in glass pan.
Pour remaining butter over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine drained vegetables, onion, cheese, mayonnaise and soup; mix well.
Pour mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top of casserole.
Return to oven and bake until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: homestyle boursin cheese
directions: Beat cream cheese and all other ingredients with electric beater until blended.
Line a margarine tub with foil and pack in mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn out on serving plate and peel off foil.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Add dry ingredients together.
Mix shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Fold together with dry ingredients. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: minestrone
directions: Slice sausage 1/2-inch thick; brown in Dutch oven with olive oil.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil; cook 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes and beef bouillon.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add Northern beans and cabbage.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: home fries
directions: Place potatoes in a pot.
Cover with water.
Boil until tender (20 to 30 minutes).
Drain and place potatoes in a bowl. Refrigerate until cool.
Cut potatoes in 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cheese, 4 eggs and sugar.
Pour over first layer.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Salt and pepper fryer.
Mix rice, water, oleo and soup.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture. Bake at 350° for 2 hours, without lifting cover.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Excellent dip and easy, too.

title: christmas punch
directions: Stir all together and put in refrigerator.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Drain water.
Add soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add mushrooms and Stove Top with juice; add onions and 1/2 of each cheese.
Mix well.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: bob wade barbecue brisket
directions: You may want to trim some fat from brisket, but leave a good amount for juice.
Soak meat in teriyaki sauce; sprinkle with Tony Chachere's seasoning, using a good amount.
Sprinkle a lot of black pepper on meat.
I do not think you can use too much.
Cover meat and put in fridge for 24 hours.
Take out and let warm up some. Re-season and marinate.
Brown meat on your choice of wood fire.
I prefer mesquite.
Remove from wood fire and wrap in aluminum foil. Put in a pan that you don't mind getting the bottom black from wood smoke and cook in oven like a roast.
When done (not overdone), put back on pit in pan; remove aluminum foil from top of brisket and smoke by using wet mesquites.
Do not have fire other than to produce smoke.
Baste with natural juices while smoking often. Turn meat over and smoke and baste the other side.
Remove from pit when meat is smoked good.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello powder; stir in all remaining ingredients.
Chill well.
Garnish with extra Cool Whip (optional).

title: country casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole.
Add chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs that have been sauteed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine milk, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly.
Add beaten eggs; cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Line bowl with vanilla wafers.
Layer with pudding, wafers and bananas.

title: chocolate toffee candy
directions: Line a cookie sheet with well buttered foil.
Place saltines, side to side, to cover.
Boil together the butter and brown sugar; pour over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with the chocolate chips; spread with spatula while hot.
They will melt.
You can also add chopped nuts or coconut on top of the chocolate.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Break into chunks when chilled.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stacy's marinated potato salad
directions: Leave skin on potatoes when boiling.
Put in large bowl when boiled and after drained.
Make the following to pour over while potatoes are still warm:
Italian salad dressing, sliced green onions and chopped parsley.
Pour over the warm bite-size potatoes and let set for about 1 hour to marinate.
Toss several times. Then add the mayonnaise.
Toss until completely covered.
Put in fridge for at least 2 hours.
Better to chill overnight so flavors have plenty of time to blend.
Just before serving, garnish with sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Great!

title: bits 'o brickle delight pie
directions: In deep bowl, using mixer, combine cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Add 3/4 cup Bits 'O Brickle; fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle remaining Bits 'O Brickle over filling. Freeze about 4 hours before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: black forest cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 45 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool in pan 25 minutes, then invert onto cooling rack to finish cooling.
Decorate and serve with 1 can cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.

title: play dough(do not eat)
directions: Mix all and have fun.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Combine fat, flour, salt, milk and broth; cook until thickened.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Cook broccoli; place in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine chicken and sauce.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until well heated and brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken casserole (mexican style)
directions: Heat onion, soups and Ro-Tel in saucepan, then in casserole dish, put layer of chicken, layer of soup mixture, layer of Doritos and top with cheese.
Bake in slow oven until mixture bubbles.

title: peanut butter swirl brownies
directions: Heat margarine until melted and remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and eggs.
Beat slightly by hand just until combined; stir in flour.
Remove 3/4 c. of batter and set aside.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining batter.
Spread chocolate batter into a greased 9 x 9 x 2 baking pan; set aside.
Stir peanut butter into reserved batter.
Dollop on top of chocolate batter, then sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Swirl batter with a knife.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: golden cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Cook grits in boiling water.
When almost done, crumble cheese and butter into grits.
Blend eggs and milk together.
Then mix egg/milk mixture with grits.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream Crisco, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add milk, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: curried tuna salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse and drain.

title: wassail
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine juices, lemonade and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add water if desired.
Serve hot or cold.

title: turkey meat balls
directions: Mix together ground turkey, egg, Stove Top seasoning, onion and Stove Top dressing.
Make small meat balls.
Brown slowly in butter.
Drain.
Add flour to drippings.
Stir until smooth. Remove from heat and add milk and water.
Cook and stir slowly until gravy is smooth.
Add meatballs to gravy.
Simmer 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: country bread pudding with custard sauce
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Pour melted butter into approximately an 8-cup baking pan and refrigerate.
Place the bread sliced into a large bowl and pour the milk over them, tossing to let the bread absorb most of the milk.
Tear sliced bread into pieces.

title: ginger sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Place by level teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: philly three-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles following directions on package.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend celery soup and milk.
Heat thoroughly in saucepan.
Add cheese to saucepan and stir until cheese is melted; then add to noodle mixture.
Turn into ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 425° uncovered for 20 mins. or until bubbly.

title: poppy chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Cool and remove from bones.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Mix soup and sour cream.
Add chicken and chopped, boiled eggs.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together flour and sugar; set aside. Grease casserole dish. Pour drained pineapple in dish. Add sugar and flour mixture to top of pineapple. Sprinkle cheese over previous layer, then the Ritz crackers. Slice margarine in small pieces and place on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: aunt dora's beef stew
directions: Stagger all of the ingredients into a large, covered, casserole.
Cover and bake in a slow oven at 225° to 250° for about 6 to 7 hours (test meat and vegetables for doneness).
Stir once after cooking 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jogging in a jar
directions: Mix all together and keep refrigerated.
Drink at least 2 ounces per day.
This will help to keep your cholesterol down as well as help those with arthritis.

title: pork chop  and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.

Stir in partially thawed potatoes and add 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions. Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange pork chops over potatoes. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: poppy seed rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add vanilla and yeast mixture.
Add one egg at a time and beat well after each addition.
Place dough in refrigerator overnight.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas by dipping in hot oil for 2-3 seconds, drain on paper towels and set aside.
In medium size bowl mix sour cream, cottage cheese and green chili; set aside.
Grate 1 cup cheese; set aside.
Cut remaining cheese into 24 slender sticks (about 1/2 x 2
inches).
Taking one tortilla shell at a time, place a stick of cheese and a heaping tablespoon of sour cream mixture on it and roll.
Place the rolled tortillas in a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Cover tortillas with enchiladas sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: potato special
directions: Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 3 tablespoons melted butter over potatoes.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream and onion. Pour over potatoes.
Mix corn flakes, 2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup grated cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cover and cook 10 minutes on High.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Roll chicken livers in flour and saute in shortening until brown.
Arrange asparagus in baking dish.
Top with sauce made from mayonnaise, minced onion and chicken livers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Brown lightly under the broiler.
The chicken livers and sauce may be prepared in advance, if desired.

title: broccoli and yellow rice casserole
directions: Simmer onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushroom soup, cheese and 1/2 cup water, heat until cheese melts.
Combine all ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions, adding a handful of brown rice to make more (optional).
While rice is cooking, skin and debone chicken and cut it in small pieces.
After rice is soft and dry, spread chicken over the top of rice along with the corn (drained); cover dish with no heat for 5 minutes.
Mix and serve.
Applesauce and biscuits go well with this dish.
